{"title_page": "Belal Muhammad", "text_new": "{{for|the American mixed martial artist|Belal Muhammad (fighter)}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name                      = Belal Muhammad\n| native_name               = \u09ac\u09c7\u09b2\u09be\u09b2 \u09ae\u09cb\u09b9\u09be\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09a6\n| native_name_lang          = Bengali\n| image                     = Belal Muhammad delivering speech.jpg\n| caption                   = Belal Muhammad at a conference in [[Sandwip]], [[Chittagong]].\n| birth_date                = {{Birth date|1936|02|20|df=y}}\n| birth_place               = Musapur, [[Sandwip]], [[Chittagong]]\n| death_date                 = {{Death date and age|df=y|2013|07|30|1936|02|20}}\n| death_place              = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]]\n| nationality               = [[Bangladesh]]i\n| notable_works             = Founder of [[Swadhin Bangla Betar Kendra]] in 1971.\n| movement                  = [[Liberation war of Bangladesh]]\n| awards                    = [[Independence Day Award]] (2010)<br>[[Bangla Academy Literary Award]] (2011)\n|parents= Mahmuda Khanom <br> Moulavi Muhammad Yaqub\n}}\n\n'''Belal Mohammad''' (20 February 1936 \u2013 30 July 2013) was one of the founders of the [[Swadhin Bangla Betar Kendra]].<ref name=dailystar>{{cite news|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/lifestyle/2009/03/04/page04.htm|title=The voice behind the scene|author=Farina Noireet|publisher=The Daily Star|date=17 March 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nMuhammad was born at Musapur Union in [[Sandwip]], [[Chittagong]]. His mother was Mahmuda Khanom and father was Moulavi Muhammad Yaqub.<ref name=media>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediavibrationbd.com/songit_peso_man_news.php?id=6|title=\u0986\u09ae\u09bf \u099c\u09c0\u09ac\u09a8\u09c7 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8\u09a6\u09bf\u09a8 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8 \u09b0\u09be\u099c\u09a8\u09c0\u09a4\u09bf \u0995\u09b0\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf|publisher=Media Vibration|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130405212709/http://mediavibrationbd.com/songit_peso_man_news.php?id=6|archivedate=2013-04-05|df=}}</ref> He was an active member of [[Bangladesh Students Union|Student Union]] of Chittagong committee in his student life.<ref name=media /> He started working as the sub-editor of ''Dainik Azadi'' in 1964 and also joined in [[Radio Pakistan]] in that year.<ref name=media /> Muhammad's wife died in 1973 and only son, Ananda, died in 1998 at the age of 32.\n\n==Liberation war in 1971==\nOn 7 March 1971, when the non-cooperation movement began with the speech from [[Sheikh Mujibur Rahman]], Mohammad was then a government officer and worked as a scriptwriter and artiste for the Radio Pakistan. He believed that the radio was a strong backbone for a nation. That is when the idea of Swadhin Bangla Betar Kendra came to his head.<ref name=dailystar />\nSince he was a radio officer, he had some experience on the subject. In those days, the [[Chittagong]] Radio station had a 10 KW transmitter, which had a radius of 50 miles listening area.<ref name=dailystar />\nBelal, along with two of his friends and co-organizers, Abdullah-Al-Faruque, Abul Kashem Sandwip, and two other unwilling engineers, who they somehow managed to convince, set out for the transmitter station at [[Kalurghat]] and founded ''Swadhin Bangla Betar Kendra''.<ref name=dailystar />\nHe was the arranger and organizer of the declaration of [[Bangladesh Liberation War|Independence of Bangladesh]] from [[Kalurghat]] betar kendra after Sheikh Mujibur Rahman had declared it and announced by Major [[Ziaur Rahman]] on behalf of Sheikh Mujib on March 27, 1971.<ref name=media /> Belal was appointed as the assistant director of the radio station on June 1, 1971.\n\n==Awards==\nMohammad was awarded [[Independence Day Award]] in 2010 for his contributions to the independence and Bangladesh Liberation War.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arts.bdnews24.com/?p=2769|title=\u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09a7\u09c0\u09a8\u09a4\u09be\u09b0 \u0998\u09cb\u09b7\u09a3\u09be: \u09ac\u09c7\u09b2\u09be\u09b2 \u09ae\u09cb\u09b9\u09be\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09a6\u09c7\u09b0 \u09b8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be\u09ce\u0995\u09be\u09b0|publisher=bdnews24.com|date=March 28, 2010}}</ref> He also received [[Bangla Academy Literary Award]] for literature on liberation war affairs in 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bangla Academy Awards 2011 go to 10|url=http://news.priyo.com/life/2012/02/19/bangla-academy-awards-2011-go-46876.html|publisher=priyo.com|date=February 19, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131216070958/http://news.priyo.com/life/2012/02/19/bangla-academy-awards-2011-go-46876.html|archivedate=December 16, 2013|df=}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nMohammad died on July 30, 2013 at the age of 77 at the Intensive Care Unit in [[Apollo Hospital Dhaka]]. He donated his body which was received by [[Sher-e-Bangla Medical College]] for the use of the medical students.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Muhammad, Belal}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Independence Day Award]]\n[[Category:People of the Bangladesh Liberation War]]\n[[Category:2013 deaths]]\n[[Category:Bengali writers]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi male writers]]\n[[Category:Recipients of Bangla Academy Award]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the American mixed martial artist|Belal Muhammad (fighter)}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name                      = Belal Muhammad\n| native_name               = \u09ac\u09c7\u09b2\u09be\u09b2 \u09ae\u09cb\u09b9\u09be\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09a6\n| native_name_lang          = Bengali\n| image                     = Belal Muhammad delivering speech.jpg\n| caption                   = Belal Muhammad at a conference in [[Sandwip]], [[Chittagong]].\n| birth_date                = {{Birth date|1936|02|20|df=y}}\n| birth_place               = Musapur, [[Sandwip]], [[Chittagong]]\n| death_date                 = {{Death date and age|df=y|2013|07|30|1936|02|20}}\n| death_place              = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]]\n| nationality               = [[Bangladesh]]i\n| notable_works             = Founder of [[Swadhin Bangla Betar Kendra]] in 1971.\n| movement                  = [[Liberation war of Bangladesh]]\n| awards                    = [[Independence Day Award]] (2010)<br>[[Bangla Academy Literary Award]] (2011)\n|parents= Mahmuda Khanom <br> Moulavi Muhammad Yaqub\n}}\n\n'''Belal Mohammad''' (20 February 1936 \u2013 30 July 2013) was one of the founders of the [[Swadhin Bangla Betar Kendra]].<ref name=dailystar>{{cite news|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/lifestyle/2009/03/04/page04.htm|title=The voice behind the scene|author=Farina Noireet|publisher=The Daily Star|date=17 March 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nMuhammad was born at Musapur Union in [[Sandwip]], [[Chittagong]]. His mother was Mahmuda Khanom and father was Moulavi Muhammad Yaqub.<ref name=media>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediavibrationbd.com/songit_peso_man_news.php?id=6|title=\u0986\u09ae\u09bf \u099c\u09c0\u09ac\u09a8\u09c7 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8\u09a6\u09bf\u09a8 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8 \u09b0\u09be\u099c\u09a8\u09c0\u09a4\u09bf \u0995\u09b0\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf|publisher=Media Vibration|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130405212709/http://mediavibrationbd.com/songit_peso_man_news.php?id=6|archivedate=2013-04-05|df=}}</ref> He was an active member of [[Bangladesh Students Union|Student Union]] of Chittagong committee in his student life.<ref name=media /> He started working as the sub-editor of ''Dainik Azadi'' in 1964 and also joined in [[Radio Pakistan]] in that year.<ref name=media /> Muhammad's wife died in 1973 and only son, Ananda, died in 1998 at the age of 32.\n\n==Liberation war in 1971==\nOn 7 March 1971, when the non-cooperation movement began with the speech from [[Sheikh Mujibur Rahman]], Mohammad was then a government officer and worked as a scriptwriter and artiste for the Radio Pakistan. He believed that the radio was a strong backbone for a nation. That is when the idea of Swadhin Bangla Betar Kendra came to his head.<ref name=dailystar />\nSince he was a radio officer, he had some experience on the subject. In those days, the [[Chittagong]] Radio station had a 10 KW transmitter, which had a radius of 50 miles listening area.<ref name=dailystar />\nBelal, along with two of his friends and co-organizers, Abdullah-Al-Faruque, Abul Kashem Sandwip, and two other unwilling engineers, who they somehow managed to convince, set out for the transmitter station at [[Kalurghat]] and founded ''Swadhin Bangla Betar Kendra''.<ref name=dailystar />\nHe was the arranger and organizer of the declaration of [[Bangladesh Liberation War|Independence of Bangladesh]] from [[Kalurghat]] betar kendra after Sheikh Mujibur Rahman had declared it and announced by Major [[Ziaur Rahman]] on behalf of Sheikh Mujib on March 27, 1971.<ref name=media /> Belal was appointed as the assistant director of the radio station on June 1, 1971.\n\n==Awards==\nMohammad was awarded [[Independence Day Award]] in 2010 for his contributions to the independence and Bangladesh Liberation War.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arts.bdnews24.com/?p=2769|title=\u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09a7\u09c0\u09a8\u09a4\u09be\u09b0 \u0998\u09cb\u09b7\u09a3\u09be: \u09ac\u09c7\u09b2\u09be\u09b2 \u09ae\u09cb\u09b9\u09be\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09a6\u09c7\u09b0 \u09b8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be\u09ce\u0995\u09be\u09b0|publisher=bdnews24.com|date=March 28, 2010}}</ref> He also received [[Bangla Academy Literary Award]] for literature on liberation war affairs in 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bangla Academy Awards 2011 go to 10|url=http://news.priyo.com/life/2012/02/19/bangla-academy-awards-2011-go-46876.html|publisher=priyo.com|date=February 19, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131216070958/http://news.priyo.com/life/2012/02/19/bangla-academy-awards-2011-go-46876.html|archivedate=December 16, 2013|df=}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nMohammad died on July 30, 2013 at the age of 77 at the Intensive Care Unit in [[Apollo Hospital Dhaka]]. He donated his body which was received by [[Sher-e-Bangla Medical College]] for the use of the medical students.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Muhammad, Belal}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Independence Day Award]]\n[[Category:People of the Bangladesh Liberation War]]\n[[Category:2013 deaths]]\n[[Category:Bengali writers]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi male writers]]\n[[Category:Recipients of Bangla Academy Award]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belal_Muhammad"}
